<p class="p">
 <italic class="italic">(1) Active Ingredient</italic>. Opium is extracted from the capsule of the opium poppy, which contains 20 to 25% alkaloids in two groups (
 <xref ref-type="fig" rid="fig11" class="xref">Figure 11</xref>):
 <list list-type="roman-lower" class="list">
  <div class="list-item" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
   <p class="p" xmlns="">Phenanthrenes (A):</p>
   <p class="p" xmlns="">
    <list list-type="order" class="list">
     <div class="list-item" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
      <p class="p" xmlns="">Morphine (5 to 20%): (a): it is the main alkaloid present in opium</p>
     </div>
     <div class="list-item" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
      <p class="p" xmlns="">Codeine (0.5 to 3%): (b)</p>
     </div>
     <div class="list-item" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
      <p class="p" xmlns="">Thebaine (0.2 to 1%): (c)</p>
     </div>
    </list>
   </p>
  </div>
  <div class="list-item" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
   <p class="p" xmlns="">Benzylisoquinolines (B):</p>
   <p class="p" xmlns="">
    <list list-type="order" class="list">
     <div class="list-item" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
      <p class="p" xmlns="">Papaverine (1%): (d)</p>
     </div>
     <div class="list-item" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
      <p class="p" xmlns="">Noscapine (2â€“10%): (e) [
       <xref rid="B52" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">52</xref>]
      </p>
     </div>
    </list>
   </p>
  </div>
 </list>
</p>
